The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 18: The government today said annexures and certificates relating to tax deducted at source, such as Form 16, are not required to be submitted along with income tax returns. The original documents and certificates may be produced by assessees as and when called for by the assessing officer, an official statement said. The credit for tax deducted at source (TDS) or tax collected at source will be allowed on the basis of details furnished in the relevant schedules of the return forms, subject to instructions on verification of TDS claims, the statement added.                            
